parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Cylinder Head/Engine Head Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cylinder head or engine head gasket can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
engine overheating
engine stalling
antifreeze fumes in the passenger compartment
puddle of antifreeze under the car
milky oil
water in the oil
cracked cylinder head
small leak of engine coolant onto the exhaust manifold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator hose can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Radiator hose blowing out
vehicle overheating
coolant leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mounts can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to a safety hazard and potentially causing the engine to fall out of the vehicle.
symptoms: Engine mounts failed
engine moves excessively when shifting gears
safety hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TCM solenoid can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to engine stalling and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Transmission malfunction
engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling
vehicle stalling at high speeds
intermittent stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when the ignition is turned off, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
smoke emits from under the hood
smoke fills the vehicle
the ignition switch is unable to be moved
the headlights remain on even when the switch is off
the battery needs to be disconnected to turn off the headlights
the turn signals and hazard lights become inoperative
the vehicle is difficult to start
the ignition switch shorts out and fills the vehicle with smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when the ignition is turned off, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
smoke emits from under the hood
smoke fills the vehicle
the electrical system malfunctions
the turn signals and hazard lights become inoperative
the headlights remain on even when the switch is off
the battery needs to be disconnected to turn off the headlights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and ignition system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is difficult to start
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor wear can lead to extended stopping distances, reduced braking performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rotors wear out prematurely
rust
and flake
causing braking performance to feel like stopping on ribbed pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out prematurely
requiring frequent replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure can lead to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS brakes lock up
causing the vehicle to slide or skid; ABS brakes fail to engage
resulting in extended stopping distances; ABS brakes release and allow the vehicle to roll forward before coming to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake hydraulic system failure can lead to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floorboard
resulting in extended stopping distances; brake pedal feels soft or spongy; brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
